Singer and songwriter Ray Ceeh was shot dead in Cape Town on Wednesday night. JOHANNESBURG - A murder investigation is underway after Zimbabwean cameraman and singer Ray Ceech was shot dead in Lentegeur, Cape Town, on Wednesday night. According to Western Cape police spokesperson Siyabulela Malo, Ceeh was reportedly dropping off passengers when the incident occurred. "Three unknown men approached his vehicle and fired one shot to his neck and he totally lost the control of his vehicle," said Malo. Ceeh, who wrote and produced his own music, is originally from Zimbabwe and was a former employee of Deen TV. The motive for the attack is unknown and no arrests have been made. Ray Ceeh - Call Me (Official Visualizer)